inedi
Class Warning

java.lang.Object
  inedi.Warning

public class Warning
extends java.lang.Object

A warning found while parsing an EDI document

Warnings are related to basic validation of the incoming EDI stream according to the corresponding transaction set schema, like a missing mandatory element, or a violation of a min/max length constraint.

Code: Code indicating the error condition

The Code property may have one of the following values:

0 (warnNone)
No problem detected
1 (warnSegCount)
The transaction set closing segment has a segment count value that doesn't match the real count.
2 (warnTranCount)
The functional group closing segment has a transaction set count value that doesn't match the real count.
3 (warnGroupCount)
The interchange closing segment has a functional group count value that doesn't match the real count.
4 (warnIXControlNum)
The interchange closing segment has an interchange control number different from the one appearing in the interchange header.
5 (warnGroupControlNum)
The group closing segment has an group control number different from the one appearing in the group header.
6 (warnTranControlNum)
The transaction set closing segment has an control number different from the one appearing in the transaction set header.
10 (warnReqElementMissing)
An mandatory element is not present in the segment.
11 (warnInvalidLength)
The element or component value has an incorrect length according to the schema.
12 (warnIDValueNotValid)
The element or component value is not one included in the list of valid values in the schema.
13 (warnReqComponentMissing)
A mandatory component is not present in the segment
30 (warnReqSegMissing)
A required segment is not present in the data stream
31 (warnReqLoopMissing)
A required loop is not present in the data stream
32 (warnMaxOccurs)
A loop or segment appears more times than allowed by the schema
33 (warnMinOccurs)
A loop or segment appears less times than allowed by the schema
40 (warnX12Paired)
At least one of the subject elements identified by the rule is not present in the segment.
41 (warnX12Required)
At least one of the subject elements identified by the rule needs to be present in the segment, but none were found.
42 (warnX12Exclusion)
Only one of the subject elements identified by the rule can be present in a single segment instance.
43 (warnX12Conditional)
The qualifier element identified by the rule is present in the segment, but one or more of the subject elements are missing.
44 (warnX12ListConditional)
The qualifier element identified by the rule is present in the segment, but none of the subject elements were present.

Message: Contains the human-readable description of the warning

Segment: The number of the segment where the warning occurred

See Also:
As1receiver, As1receiver.Warning
